description: Observability and tracing rules for Micrometer + WebFlux + WebClient
globs: src/main/java/**/*.java, src/main/resources/application*.yml
alwaysApply: false
---

# Observability Rules

- Use Micrometer Observation as the primary application-level observability API.
- Prefer ObservationRegistry and Observation in business code.
- Avoid direct tracer/span APIs unless there is a specific low-level need.
- Add business observations only at meaningful boundaries:
  - use-case execution
  - external HTTP integration
  - expensive fallback path
- Do not create spans for every method.
- Never put IDs in low-cardinality tags.
- Put IDs only in high-cardinality tags when truly needed.
- For WebClient, always use injected WebClient.Builder.
- Never use WebClient.create(...).
- Use URI templates instead of string concatenation.
- Preserve trace correlation in logs.
- Keep spring.reactor.context-propagation enabled.
